This paper deals with image classification and detection tasks using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of the scattering transform, which is a mathematical tool used in signal processing, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the ImageNet dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision research, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of detection tasks, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
